UID:0d82f781-e756-55d6-815b-ced53eea6de2
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250127T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250127T161500
DESCRIPTION:Click the link to register: https://forms.gle/JyBzem7eitvTHMCk
 7\n\n \n\nTKE Community Schools Program SY24/25 \n\nSusitna Valley Littl
 e Dribblers Basketball Camp (1st-3rd Grade) Registration\n\nEvent Location
 :  TKE Gymnasium\nDays of the Week: Mondays and Wednesdays\nPractice Tim
 e: 3:05 - 4:30 pm\nPractice Begin Date: Monday\, January 6\, 2025\n\nPra
 ctice End Date: Wednesday\, February 12\, 2025\n\nNO PRACTICE ON: Monday
 \, January 20th and Monday\, February 10th\n\n \n\nCrowley Classic Tourna
 ment Date and Game Time: Saturday\, February 14\, 2025\, game time TBA \
 n\nTournament Location: Susitna Valley Jr/Sr High School Gymnasium\n\n \
 n\nProgram Cost: $20 per athlete\n\nEach registered athlete will take hom
 e one intermediate size basketball at the end of the season.\n\n \n\nPers
 onalized jerseys will be available for purchase for an additional $15.00. 
 Jerseys will be available for purchase on-site. \n\n \n\nPayment details
  are pending. We will let you know as soon as possible how this will be ha
 ndled. Thank you for your patience and understanding.\n\n \n\nA refund wi
 ll be considered for all circumstances. If a student is removed from Baske
 tball Camp due to behavioral issues\, a refund will be issued.\n\n \n\nAc
 tion Needed: \n\nComplete the online registration form to sign up. \n\n
  \n\nThe Matanuska-Susitna Borough School District Release of Liability F
 orm must be completed by a parent or guardian prior to athlete participati
 on. A digital copy of the completed form may be emailed to Ms. Becks at re
 becca.hrdy@matsuk12.us\, or a printed paper copy may be turned in by the 
 first practice. Paper copies will also be available in the front office.\n
 \nLittleDribblersRM11StudentPermissionSliptoParticipate.pdf\n\n \n\nRegis
 tration is due by the first day of practice.\n\n \n\nEnter your student's
  practices into https://parents.pikmykid.com//. \n\n \n\nDescription: 
 \n\nThis program fills quickly on a first-come\, first-served basis. The 
 camp will be capped at 30 athletes. We will contact you if the camp is ful
 l.\n\n \n\nStudent Conduct: Students are expected to be well-behaved at 
 all times. This camp is for athletes who are serious about having fun\, de
 veloping a love for basketball\, and improving skills. If a child’s beh
 avior creates any disruption for any reason\, the parent will be contacted
  to remove him/her immediately and the child may not be allowed back into 
 the camp in future years. You will be refunded your entry fee. \n\n \n\
 nEmergencies: If an emergency arises which will delay you picking up your
  son or daughter on time\, please call or text the Coordinator of Basketb
 all Camp Program\, Alysa Tunnell\, at (907) 355-3497. \n\n \n\nFor the
  safety of your child\, no student will be released to anyone except a par
 ent or guardian unless the student brings a signed and detailed note fro
 m the parent or guardian telling us otherwise. If an emergency arises\, p
 lease call us at the number listed above.\n\n 
LOCATION:TKE Gym
SUMMARY:CANCELLED TKE CS: Susitna Valley Little Dribblers Basketball Camp (
 1st-3rd Grade)
END:VEVENT
