BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053942Z
UID:dfacbf8c-5a40-5b76-9110-dc570b80bd49
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250217T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250217T090000
DESCRIPTION:Dear Talkeetna Elementary Families\,\n\nAs you are aware\, our 
 school has experienced eight snow days this year\, and we must adjust our 
 calendar to ensure that our students receive the required instructional ti
 me needed to support their learning. The following dates will now be regul
 ar school days when students are expected to attend:\n\n\n	 \n	February 
 17 (Previously a Parent-Teacher Conference day)\n	March 7 (Previously a 
 Teacher Work Day)\n	May 2 (Previously a Professional Learning Day)\n	May 
 21 (Previously a Scheduled Snow Day)\n	May 23 (Previously a Teacher Work
  Day)\n\n\nPlease note that this adjustment includes one additional studen
 t contact day at the end of the school year.\n\nWe understand that these c
 hanges may present challenges for some families\, and we sincerely appreci
 ate your patience and flexibility as we navigate this unusual school year.
  Our goal is to ensure that our students continue to receive the education
  they deserve while meeting the required instructional hours.\n\nIn additi
 on to these changes\, we recognize the importance of Parent-Teacher Confer
 ences. To make up for the loss of our previously scheduled conferences\, t
 eachers will be contacting families to arrange phone conferences. We will 
 prioritize Reads Act conversations for Tier 2 and Tier 3 students. Please 
 look for an informational letter in your students homework folder next wee
 k. \n\nThank you for your understanding and support as we work together t
 o make the best of these adjustments. If you have any questions or concern
 s\, please do not hesitate to reach out to the school office.\n\nSincerely
 \,\nDrew Larrabee\nPrincipal\, Talkeetna Elementary School
LOCATION:Talkeetna Elementary School\, E Timberwolf Loop\, Talkeetna\, AK\,
  USA
SUMMARY:TKE School Day: Snow Day Make-Up
END:VEVENT
