BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053942Z
UID:25b5d6a3-4a5e-5818-86ec-12d4421e934c
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250324
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250329
DESCRIPTION:School Safety Week March 24 - 28\nDuring the week of March 24th
 -March 28th MSBSD is promoting Safety Week! Safety Week provides an opport
 unity for students\, school staff\, and community members to participate i
 n activities\, events\, and conversations regarding issues affecting schoo
 l safety.\n\nWhether it is getting students to develop evacuation plans fo
 r their homes or how to dress properly for outdoor conditions\, Safety Wee
 k is an opportunity to discuss many topics\, customizable to your school o
 r student needs. Some ideas to get the ball rolling:\n\n  *   Remind your 
 school community about See It\, Stop It\n  *   Invite one or more professi
 onals in law enforcement\, mental health\, social work\, or health care to
  educate students about the negative impact of substance and alcohol abuse
  in minors.\n  *   Invite parents and news media to your school to highlig
 ht the positive things at school that students are doing to prevent violen
 ce.\n  *   Organize a youth roundtable on student safety. Encourage studen
 ts to share their safety ideas with school administration.\n  *   Invite f
 irst responders to make presentations to students on personal safety\, fir
 e safety\, or transportation safety.\n  *   Celebrate Everyday Heroes. Hav
 e students nominate staff or peers that have been helpful above and beyond
  good citizenship. Announce the nominees and have recognition for them. Co
 nsider reaching out to a local business to donate prizes or food.\n\nI kno
 w with your help and commitment we as a district can raise awareness about
  important safety considerations in our communities. A list of community r
 esources is linked here. Also\, don’t forget to hang your Safety Week Ba
 nner that was delivered to your school to be displayed March 24-28! (Point
  of Contact: Rusty Belanger\, MSBSD Safety and Security Manager)\n\n\n\nRu
 sty Belanger\n\n“Discretion will protect you\, and understanding will gu
 ard you.”\n\n\nRusty Belanger – Safety and Security Manager\nMatanuska
 -Susitna Borough School District\nPh: 907-761-4031 Cell: 907-317-9589 Fax:
  907-864-2081\nEmail: steven.belanger@matsuk12.us or rusty.belanger@matsuk
 12.us\n\n
LOCATION:outside planter box
SUMMARY:Hang Banner School Safety Week March 24 - 28
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
