BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053943Z
UID:0205023f-a1d0-520f-b23e-394d591ac993
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250414T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250414T170000
DESCRIPTION:Good morning\,I wanted to check in to see if you might know of 
 any parents or community members who would be willing to provide testimony
  in support of SB 82\, the Governor’s Education Bill\, during the upcomi
 ng Senate Education Committee hearing. The hearing is scheduled for Monday
 \, April 14\, from 3:30 to 5:00 p.m.\, with about an hour reserved for ope
 n public testimony.While we all agree on the importance of increasing the 
 Base Student Allocation (BSA)\, SB 82 also includes several targeted provi
 sions that strengthen public school choice—something I know your schools
  work hard to support and expand. I've attached the presentation Deena gav
 e to the committee on February 24 for your reference and potential talking
  points.Thank you so much for everything you do—for your schools\, your 
 families\, and Alaska’s broader public school choice community. I hope y
 ou have a great end to the school year!Sincerely\,Monica
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:Testimony on the Governor’s Education Bill SB 82
END:VEVENT
