BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053943Z
UID:ffc6e895-6b0f-514b-937a-e341cee7f643
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250418T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250418T140000
DESCRIPTION:This musical is based on a beloved Eastern folk story that teac
 hes children the value of sharing and caring for each other by showing how
  a group of visitors trick the villagers into sharing their provisions\, a
 nd in the end\, everyone gets together to share one big pot of soup. Amie 
 Devine &amp\; Rachel Kroon will help the story come to life with singing\,
  dancing\, and acting. The actors and actresses will dress up like village
 rs with jeans or skirts and white shirts with aprons or hats\, OR soldiers
  with black pants and shirts and red sashes. Once the sign up deadline is 
 reached\, Director Amie Devine will send out a script and videos of the so
 ngs for the students to practice with at home. They will be rewarded if th
 ey come to the first day of camp familiar with the content of the play. We
  have found that this format has proven to be quite successful when we onl
 y have a week to prepare for the performance.LOCATION: MCS Deshka A&amp\;B
  - River Wing
LOCATION:MCS Deshka A\; MCS Deshka B
SUMMARY:Musical Theater Camp for K-3: Stone Soup - a 'Rock' Opera
RRULE:FREQ=DAILY;UNTIL=20250418T200000Z;INTERVAL=1
END:VEVENT
