BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053943Z
UID:d82eb116-c958-56dd-b21a-42e169043561
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250424T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250424T124500
DESCRIPTION:We begin with Aesop’s classic fable of The Tortoise and the H
 are but continue the story which finds them 10 years down the road\, now w
 ith children of their own and exploring modern day distractions. Smart pho
 nes and video games create a new landscape of lost connections to life exp
 eriences. The Next Gen features Tortoise Junior and Lil’ Hare in a whole
  new kind of race\; where their adventures lead them into unexpected terri
 tory. Old man Tortoise and Big Daddy Hare must come together despite their
  differences to find and save their children. What hurdles will they have 
 to overcome to make it to the finish line?\nWith dazzling visuals\, poigna
 nt storytelling and the creative use of music from classical to pop\, this
  production brings this tale into a new brilliant light.\nItinerary\, Apri
 l 24:\n\n  *   9:05 AM check in at Mat-Su Central School (New school build
 ing\, 2055 Stringfield Rd. Palmer)\n  *   9:15 AM depart on the school bus
 \n  *   10:30 - 11:30 AM showtime\n  *   12:45 PM arrive back at Mat-Su Ce
 ntral School\n  *   Families are welcome to ride the school bus or meet us
  at the Performing Arts Center in Anchorage. Students can attend with a pa
 rent or without. MCS staff chaperones will monitor the group.\n\nCost: Stu
 dent and adult tickets are $22 per person. Student and one parent ticket p
 rice will be deducted from the student(s) allotment. Additional parents or
  family members\, will pay by credit card through "School Pay". A payment 
 link will be sent directly to your email address.\nMCS Student Permission 
 Slip\n\n\n
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:ADVENTURES OF TORTOISE AND THE HARE
END:VEVENT
