DESCRIPTION:Join Miss Angie and your Kinder KickStart friends on a fun fiel
 d trip to the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center. We’ll learn about Ala
 ska animals on a guided walking tour and end the day with a Alaska Animal 
 Puppet show! Such fun!12:00 PM Arrive at AK WCC12:15 PM Welcome and Expect
 ations12:30 PM Guided Walking Tour1:40 PM AK Puppet Show2:30 PM Depart AK 
 WCCSpecial instructions: Wear comfortable walking shoes\, bring a coat and
  sack lunch.Transportation: We will not have school bus transportation for
  this field trip. Parents will meet us at the Alaska Wildlife Conservation
  Center\, 43520 Seward Highway\, Girdwood\, AKStudent Cost: Mat Su Central
  School will cover the admittance cost for all Kinder KickStart students. 
 Yay! Additional siblings' admission cost is $6.25  (this can be automatica
 lly deducted from their MCS allotment)Adult Cost: $24 per person
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:KKS Field Trip to Wildlife Conservation Center
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
