BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053943Z
UID:14de0f53-ff9d-5c84-a41c-130c8b8cda4e
DTSTART;TZID=America/Juneau:20250505T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Juneau:20250505T100000
DESCRIPTION:"Drive Your Tractor to Work Day" is a fun\, community event whe
 re residents and visitors are encouraged to drive their tractors to work o
 r other destinations in Palmer. The parade route goes through town\, start
 ing at the fairgrounds and ending at the depot. This event is a way for th
 e community to celebrate its agricultural roots and have some fun.[cid:b62
 2537c-a7f3-4488-8ef2-07eae191a401]The Annual 2025 Drive Your Tractor to Wo
 rk Day event is celebrating the start of farming season for our Alaskan fa
 rmers! The Palmer celebration and tractor parade will be on Monday\, May 5
 th starting at 9:00The Parade of Tractors will depart from the State Fairg
 rounds at approximately 9 a.m. and proceed along Outer Springer to S Chuga
 ch St. From there they will make their way to S Valley Way and head along 
 the Grow Palmer edible rail trail (a great spot for viewing the parade!) T
 he Tractors will turn at Blueberry Ave and head back through downtown Palm
 er on S. Alaska Street. We will finish at the Palmer Pavillion where our f
 armers and tractor drivers will enjoy an all Alaska Grown breakfast and fa
 milies can meet their local farmers!Drive Your Tractor to Work Day is desi
 gned to celebrate the upcoming season and give our farmers the recognition
  they deserve for working so hard to feed us. Show your support by sharing
  this event\, posting pictures of you and your tractor\, and remembering t
 o BUY LOCAL whenever you can.This event is brought to you by Alaska Farmla
 nd Trust and Glacier Valley Farm with sponsorship and support from the Cit
 y of Palmer\, Country Financial\, and Matanuska Electric Association.
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:🚜 Drive Your Tractor to Work Day
END:VEVENT
