BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260308T053944Z
UID:58a29906-a82f-557a-87cd-f5c319ff7907
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250615
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250616
DESCRIPTION:Most people think Father’s Day was made up by greeting card c
 ompanies—but it wasn’t!\nThe idea came from Sonora Smart Dodd in 1909.
  After hearing a Mother’s Day sermon\, she thought dads deserved a speci
 al day too—especially her own dad\, who raised six kids by himself.\nThe
  first Father’s Day was celebrated in 1910 in Spokane\, Washington. Some
  U.S. presidents supported it\, but it took a long time to become official
 . People joked that dads didn’t want a holiday and said they’d rather 
 have a “National Fishing Day.”\nSonora kept pushing for decades. Final
 ly\, in 1972\, President Nixon made Father’s Day a national holiday—ov
 er 60 years after it was first suggested!\nThanks to Sonora\, we now celeb
 rate dads every year on the third Sunday in June.\n
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:👨 Father's Day
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
