UID:0c4f39ba-0a77-5e61-b83e-b1723da5a8f5
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250912
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250914
DESCRIPTION: \n\n[https://files.constantcontact.com/2b412c26101/6f967971-
 1b17-4547-88be-7eacf3e9eda9.png?rdr=true]\n\nRegistration is Open for\nAAS
 B's Statewide Charter School Academy –\n﻿September 12-13\, 2025!\n\n
  \n\nWhen?\nSeptember 12-13\, 2025\, in Anchorage\n·    Friday\, Septem
 ber 12:\nMorning – Charter School Principals\nAfternoon – APC Members 
 &amp\; Principals\n·    Saturday\, September 13: APC Members &amp\; Princ
 ipals\n\nWhat?\nAASB is partnering with the Anchorage School District for 
 this year’s Charter School Academy. Join us September 12-13\, 2025\, in 
 Anchorage for AASB's Statewide Charter School Academy – the only statewi
 de dedicated conference for Alaska Charter School leaders! The Statewide C
 harter School Academy is a statewide training for charter school principal
 s and academic policy committee (APC) members.\n\nThis academy is designed
  to support APC members in working together with their school and district
  to promote educational excellence while connecting and learning from char
 ter schools around the state.\n\nThis event will provide APC members and p
 rincipals with the opportunity to:\n\n·    Build your skills &amp\; knowl
 edge in areas such as Roles &amp\; Responsibilities\, Effective Meetings\,
  communication\, and more.\n\n·    Connect with peers from other Alaska C
 harter Schools to exchange ideas and strategies that strengthen local gove
 rnance and student outcomes.\n\nTopics Will Include:\n\n·    Your Roles a
 nd Responsibilities\n·    Understanding your Contractual Agreements &amp\
 ; Bylaws\n·    Holding an Effective Meeting\n·    Communication with you
 r School Communities\n·    Onboarding APC Members\n·    Goal Setting\n·
     AND MORE!\n\n \n\nRates\n\nRegular AASB Members:\n$390 for Principal
 s (2 days)\n$240 for APC Members\nAffiliate AASB Members:\n$470 for Princi
 pals (2 days)\n$290 for APC Members\n\n \n\nMore Information\n\n \n\nQ
 uestions? Contact Jenni Lefing.\n\nPlease Note: Anchorage School District 
 APC Members and Principals do not need to register via this link. They sho
 uld reach out to their district contact.\n\n \n\nAASB's Mission\nTo advo
 cate for children and youth by assisting school boards in providing qualit
 y\n﻿public education\, focused on student achievement\, through effectiv
 e local governance.\n\naasb.org | Email | (907) 463-1660\n\n[Email] [Faceb
 ook]    [LinkedIn]    [Web]    [X] \n\n \n\n
LOCATION:Anchorage
SUMMARY:AASB Charter School Academy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
