UID:3ffa0e60-6e60-53c0-bffb-72aca668c8ef
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260113
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260117
DESCRIPTION:The annual student password change will take place on the morni
 ng of Tuesday\, January 20th after 8am\, for students who have not changed
  their password since July 1\, 2025. We recommend that students change the
 ir password prior to Tuesday\, January 20th – they will not have to chan
 ge again if they complete this ahead of time. This means:\n\n  *   K-2 Stu
 dents: The password will remain ‘alaska’. No action is needed.\n  *   
 3rd Grade Students: They will need to change their passwords from ‘alask
 a’ (or whatever they currently set it to) to a new\, unique password.\n 
  *   Grades 4-12: They will be required to change their password.\n  *   N
 ew-to-District Students: They will need to change their password using the
 ir username as their old password.\n\nStudents can check when they last ch
 anged their password:\n\n  *   Visit: https://myaccount.google.com/securit
 y\n  *   Scroll down to ‘How you sign in to Google’ section and look f
 or Password row\, it will say when it was last changed (if it doesn’t sh
 ow a year then it means the current year)\n\nStudents who know their old p
 assword can do the following:\n\n  *   Use the MSBSD Password Help option 
 on a Chromebook\, located in the lower left corner of the login screen\, o
 r use the MSBSD Password Help\, Option 1.\n\n  *   It is recommended that 
 students setup their password recovery tools if they haven’t done so alr
 eady. This option is available on the MSBSD Password Help\, Option 3.\n\nS
 tudents who DO NOT know their old password will need help from your buildi
 ng’s designated staff or if they have setup the recovery tools\, use MSB
 SD Password Help\, Option 2.\n\n  *   Your designated building staff who w
 ere provided rights to the Password Change Utility can also help change pa
 sswords for students with unique circumstances.\n\nRemember to check that 
 students are following the password requirements:\n\n  *   Grades 3-8\n   
   *   8 Characters\n  *   Grades 9-12\n     *   8 Characters\n     *   At 
 least one character from 3 of the 4 groups (uppercase\, lowercase\, number
 \, special character)\n     *   Your last 5 passwords can’t be re-used\n
      *   Cannot contain your first or last name\n     *   If similar passw
 ord is used\, must change at least 3 characters\n\nIf you do not recall wh
 o in your school was provided rights to the Password Change Utility\, plea
 se check this page: School Management - User Permissions\nIf you want to r
 equest to have the ability to change student passwords\, please ask your b
 uilding administrator(s) to request access using the link above.\n\nIT Dep
 artment | Mat-Su Borough School District\n501 North Gulkana\, Palmer\, AK 
 99645\nOffice: (907) 761-HELP | Fax: (907) 746-9288 | CallCenter@matsuk12.
 us\n\n\n
LOCATION:High Importance!!!
SUMMARY:Annual student password change (see notes) 
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
