DESCRIPTION:Opportunity to Celebrate and Publicize for School Choice WeekLA
 URA RICHARDSON​​​​SUSAN MCCAULEY\;​​​TIFFANY TRICE\;​​
 ​BARBARA GERARD\;​​​AUSTIN GRIMES\;​​​PATRICIA FARREN\;​
 ​​SANDY PEREZ\;​​​JASON MOEN\;​​​AMY HARREN\;​​​JOHN
  WEETMAN\;​​​ERIC RAINS\;​​​TYLER GILLIGAN\;​​​MICHELLE 
 SANDE\;​​​JASON MOORE\;​​​NATHAN CHUD​​​​​​JOHN NO
 TESTINE\;​​​KENDRA BARTZ​​Dear School Leaders-Yesterday\, Patti 
 Farren\, Michelle Sande (from Mat-Su Central) and I met with Alaska School
  Choice Coalition leader Leigh Sloan about School Choice Week coming in Ja
 nuary 2026! There are two opportunities I’d like to share with you.First
 \, Mat-Su Central and American Charter invite you to join us in having a p
 resence at:Alaska School Choice ExpoSaturday\, January 31\, 202611 AM-2 PM
 Alaska Native Heritage Centerhttps://alaskaschoolchoice.com/At the school 
 fair\, you’ll (a community attendee) have the chance to meet representat
 ives from traditional public\, public charter\, public magnet\, private\, 
 faith-based\, online\, home\, and nontraditional schooling options\, and h
 ave your questions answered.To participate with a table at the School Choi
 ce expo\, please reach out to Laura Richardson with your commitment (MSBSD
  has two additional tables purchased for this event—first come\, first s
 erved. MCS and American Charter also have tables purchased already). Alter
 natively\, you can register and purchase your own table here:  https://ala
 skaschoolchoice.com/vendors/ (early bird pricing is $50 until October 31. 
 Starting November 1\, table pricing goes up to $100.)The SECOND opportunit
 y for celebration during School Choice Week is this:Alaska Students Shine 
 AssemblyMonday\, January 26\, 20261:00 pm – 2:00 pmKing’s Chapel (King
 ’s Alaska)Wasilla Main Auditorium3301 E. Parks Hwy.\, Wasilla\, AK 99654
 https://schoolchoiceweek.com/events/alaska-students-shine-assembly/Plans f
 or the Alaska Students Shine assembly are under way. I will share more det
 ails as they come available.I hope you all have a wonderful Halloween! Wel
 come to November and a fall full of things to be thankful for. 😊Laura R
 ichardsonFamily &amp\; Community Partnership Coordinator\,Mat-Su Central S
 chool Liaison and RecruiterOffice of Teaching and Learning\, Matanuska-Sus
 itna Borough School DistrictPh: 907-761-4050laura.richardson@matsuk12.us
LOCATION:
SUMMARY:
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
