DESCRIPTION:Congratulations!Your student has been selected to represent Twi
 ndly Bridge Charter School at the MSBSDElementary School District Chess To
 urnament. I am proud of their hard work\, sportsmanship\,and dedication to
  chess this season.Tournament InformationGrades 3–5�� Saturday\, Apr
 il⏰ 8:00 AM – 2:30 PM�� Colony Middle SchoolParents are not requir
 ed to stay and will not be allowed in the competition room or to watchindi
 vidual matches. However\, families are welcome to wait in the cafeteria an
 d are encouragedto attend the final awards ceremony around 2pm.Parents/gua
 rdians are responsible for drop-off and pick-up at Colony Middle School.Lu
 nch will be provided. Please let me know if your child has any food allerg
 ies or dietaryrestrictions.If your child has been selected as an alternate
 \, I will notify families by March 20 if additionaltournament spots become
  available.If your student is unable to attend\, please let me know as soo
 n as possible so I can adjustthe roster and offer the opportunity to an al
 ternate player.Thank you\, and congratulations again!MaryCatherine Harmon2
 026 Twindly Bridge Tournament TeamMason BilleciLuke HarmonTeagan GliddenRu
 th E. RormanScarlett LauferHenry Griesinger- 1st AlternateDavid Bolte - 2n
 d Alternate
LOCATION:Colony Middle School (9250 E Bogard Rd\, Palmer\, AK 99645\, Unite
 d States)
SUMMARY:Elementary School District Chess Tournament
